title: Album Page, "Houses on Rue de la Concorde, Havre", June 4–5, 1887
medium: Graphite on thick cream wove paper tipped into binding with fabric
inscribed: Recto, in graphite, upper right corner: 14; lower right corner: 15; below drawing at right: Houses at Havre / Rue de la Concorde / June 4.5 1887.  Many numbers scrawled perpendicular to drawing along right edge of sheet.
description: Horizontal sheet cut down at the top and mounted centrally in the binding.  Depicted are the corners of two blocks with a small alley between them.  The buildings are late medieval or Renaissance in origin with later additions.  They are masonry at the first story with timber above.  The rooflines are irregular, punctuated by windows with large dormers and many chimney stacks. The street level of the building at the write is labeled EPICERIE DUVAL SP....

tombstone.epitaph: Album Page, "Houses on Rue de la Concorde, Havre", June 4–5, 1887.Graphite on thick cream wove paper tipped into binding with fabric. Gift of Mrs. William Greenough. 1943-51-188.
